Title of the paper : Single-cell RNA sequencing reveals the heterogeneity of liver-resident immune cells in human

Details about The Samples and Processing

CD45+ immune cells are derived from healthy human liver, spleen and PBMCs from 3 donors access to liver transplantation. scRNA-seq libraries was prepared using 10x Genomics protocols and sequenced on Illumina HiSeq X Ten platform.

Figure 1: the overall clustering of immune cell populations derived from the samples.

CD45_cell.ident <- read.table(file = "GSE125188_CD45+_cell_identities.tsv.gz", sep = "\t", header = F, row.names = 1, skip = 1)
colnames(CD45_cell.ident) <- "clusters"

CD45.srt@meta.data$clusters <-  CD45.srt@meta.data$clusters %>% as.factor() 
CD45.srt <- SetIdent(CD45.srt, value = "clusters")
CD45.srt <- subset(CD45.srt, subset = clusters != "NA")

cell type annotation

#assigning cell types to clusters according to the expression of typical markers
CD45.srt_markers$cell_markers <- 
  case_when(CD45.srt_markers$gene %in% c("CD3D", "KLRF1") ~ "NK & T",
            CD45.srt_markers$gene %in% "CD19" ~ "B",
            CD45.srt_markers$gene %in% "SDC1" ~ "PC",
            CD45.srt_markers$gene %in% c("CD14", "FCGR3A") ~ "Myeloid",
            TRUE ~ "none")

CD45.srt_anno <- CD45.srt_markers %>% 
  filter(CD45.srt_markers$cell_markers != "none")

##rename clusters with cell type
CD45.srt <- RenameIdents(CD45.srt, '1' = 'Myeloid', `2` = 'B', `3` = 'B', `4` = 'NK & T', `5` = 'NK & T', `6` = 'B', `7` =  'NK & T', `8` = 'NK & T', `9` = 'Myeloid', `10` = 'NK & T', `11` = 'PC', `12` = 'NK & T', `13` = 'Myeloid', `14` = 'NK & T', `15` = 'PC', `16` = 'NK & T', `17` = 'PC', `18` = 'NK & T', `19` = 'B', `20` = 'NK & T' , '21' = 'Myeloid' , '22' = 'B' , '23' = 'PC' , '24' = 'Myeloid' , '25' = 'Myeloid')

##assigning tissue and donor
CD45.srt@meta.data <- 
  CD45.srt@meta.data %>% mutate(donor = case_when(str_detect(rownames(CD45.srt@meta.data), c("-1|-4|-7")) ~ "donor 1",
                                                  str_detect(rownames(CD45.srt@meta.data),c("-2|-5|-8")) ~ "donor 2",
                                                  str_detect(rownames(CD45.srt@meta.data),c("-3|-6|-9")) ~ "donor 3"))
                              
CD45.srt@meta.data <- 
  CD45.srt@meta.data %>% mutate(tissue = case_when(str_detect(rownames(CD45.srt@meta.data), c("-1|-2|-3")) ~ "blood",
                                                  str_detect(rownames(CD45.srt@meta.data),c("-4|-5|-6")) ~ "spleen",
                                                  str_detect(rownames(CD45.srt@meta.data),c("-7|-8|-9")) ~ "LP"))

CD45.srt@meta.data <- CD45.srt@meta.data %>% 
  mutate(donor = as.factor(donor)) %>% 
  mutate(tissue = factor(tissue, levels = c("blood", "spleen", "LP")))

  rownames_to_column(var = "gene") %>%

C7_m <- FindMarkers(cycling.srt, ident.1 = "C7-cycling" ,test.use = "MAST")

## Combining coefficients and standard errors
## Calculating log-fold changes
## Calculating likelihood ratio tests

C7_m <- C7_m %>% arrange(avg_log2FC)
gene_list <- C7_m %>% pull(avg_log2FC)
gene_list <- gene_list/log10(2)
names(gene_list) <- rownames(C7_m)

pathway <- qusage::read.gmt("h.all.v7.5.1.symbols.gmt")
fgseaRes <- fgsea(pathways = pathway , stats = gene_list, scoreType = "std")
table <- head(fgseaRes[order(padj),])

#pdf("f3g.pdf")

table %>% 
  mutate(pathway = reorder(pathway, -padj)) %>% 
  mutate(padj = -1*log10(padj)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = padj, y=pathway, col = NES))+
  geom_point(size = 5)+
  labs(x = "-log10 (p.adjust)", y = "", col = "")+
  scale_x_continuous(trans='log10')+
  scale_colour_gradient2(low = "blue", high = "red", mid = "white", guide = "colourbar")
